# Project-wide shellcheck exceptions. Each disable is deliberate — see the
# comment above it. Prefer adding here over scattering inline
# `# shellcheck disable=` comments so individual scripts stay clean.

# SC2012: "Use find instead of ls to better handle non-alphanumeric filenames."
# The pipeline consistently uses `ls -t <dir>/*.mkv | head -n 1` to pick the
# most recently modified file (mtime-sort-then-take-first). All filenames in
# these directories are produced by the pipeline itself (seg###.mkv,
# *_STABLE.mkv, vhs-env-<timestamp>, etc.) — no embedded newlines or other
# pathological characters `ls` would mis-handle. Rewriting to
# `find -printf '%T@ %p\n' | sort -rn | ...` for every call site is a larger,
# riskier change to core file-selection logic for a purely theoretical benefit
# here; the existing quoting already handles spaces correctly.
disable=SC2012
